END WITH A COMPLETE SENTENCE AND A PERIOD (.)

The 1980s saw the introduction of the Internet Protocol (IP), which allowed different networks to communicate with each other, forming the modern internet.  The World Wide Web (WWW) was invented in 1989 by Tim Berners-Lee, revolutionizing the internet with user-friendly web pages and hyperlinks. The 1990s witnessed widespread adoption of the internet, with the emergence of internet service providers (ISPs) and web browsers like Netscape Navigator. As technology advanced, high-speed internet and mobile devices became ubiquitous, transforming the way people communicate, access information, and conduct daily activities.
